page.title: 01South west tip, Guernsey.
page.content: The area which we are studying is Torteval on the south western coast of Guernsey, Channel Islands. The area is mostly sea surrounding a highland area consisting of residential and farmland sections. The coastland is mostly steep cliffs, the highest point being one hundred and seven metres above mean sea level. At the very tip of Pleinmont Point there is land owned by The National Trust of Guernsey which has several public paths, popular with tourists. Inland the area consists mostly of farms, residential housing and pasture.
